What is an Internet Gateway (IGW)? ğŸŒ
An Internet Gateway (IGW) is a bridge between your VPC and the Internet. It allows resources in a public subnet to communicate with the internet.

How IGW Works?
ğŸ“¤ Outbound Traffic â€“ Instances in a public subnet send requests to the internet (e.g., fetching data from a website).
ğŸ“¥ Inbound Traffic â€“ Users on the internet can access services hosted in a public subnet (e.g., a web application).

Key Points About IGW
âœ… Required for Public Subnets â€“ Without an IGW, instances canâ€™t connect to the internet.
âœ… One IGW Per VPC â€“ A VPC can only have one Internet Gateway.
âœ… Needs Route Table Configuration â€“ Public subnets must have a route to the IGW.

